===Etymology 1===
Sense of sleeping berth possibly from Scottish English {{m|en|bunker||seat, bench}}, origin is uncertain but possibly Scandinavian.
Confer Old Swedish {{m|gmq-osw|bunke||boards used to protect the cargo of a ship}}.
See also {{m|en|boarding}}, {{m|en|flooring}} and confer {{m|en|bunch}}.

